Princess Diana rubs elbows with Washington elite at embassy luncheon 
Britain's Princess Diana rubbed elbows with Washington's power elite
Saturday -- including First Lady Hillary Clinton and General Colin
Powell -- at a British embassy luncheon.
British Ambassador Sir Robin Renwick and his wife Lady Annie Renwick
hosted the event to honor the princess who is in the United States on a
private visit.
Princess Diana was visiting the US capital for the weekend as the guest
of Brazilian Ambassador Paulo Tarso Flecha de Lima and his wife Lucia,
who has been a friend of Diana since the two met in Brazil in 1991.
Other personalities who attended the two-hour luncheon included the
vice president's wife, Tipper Gore; actor Michael York, and Saudi
Ambassador Prince Bandar Bin Sultan, according to an embassy spokesman.
